                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="52737" author="emoly.liu" created="Wed, 20 Feb 2013 05:04:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;b2_1 port is at &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/5474&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/5474&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="51866" author="bfaccini" created="Wed, 6 Feb 2013 09:50:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Status as fixed since not reported with Lustre-1.8/EL5 and Master patch should be ok for all 2.x versions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="50264" author="bfaccini" created="Thu, 10 Jan 2013 09:37:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I submitted patch #3 according to Andreas comment to better add missing kfree()s of s_mb_prealloc_table, in patch ext4-prealloc-rhel6.patch where it was introduced.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I did not submit a new patch against ext4-&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;prealloc,malloc&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;-rhel5.patch for master since it seems we don&apos;t build master Server distros for rhel5, am I right ? Or do I need to do it anyway, at least for 1.8 ?&lt;/p&gt;



</comment>
                            <comment id="48722" author="bfaccini" created="Tue, 4 Dec 2012 05:53:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch Set 2 looks better ..., I verified that after &quot;mount &lt;del&gt;t ldiskfs/umount/sync/drop_caches&quot;, super_block&lt;/del&gt;&amp;gt;s_fs_info&amp;gt;s_mb_prealloc_table was freed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="48702" author="bfaccini" created="Mon, 3 Dec 2012 17:09:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oops, just submitted patch set 2 ..., because I forgot some rules to patch a patch !!!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="48413" author="bfaccini" created="Tue, 27 Nov 2012 11:17:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Master patch submitted at &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/4683&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/4683&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="48338" author="bfaccini" created="Sat, 24 Nov 2012 03:27:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello Oleg,&lt;br/&gt;
Just for my understanding did you find this by monitoring the slabs usage or by browsing the source code ??&lt;br/&gt;
Thank&apos;s.&lt;br/&gt;
Bruno.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="48308" author="pjones" created="Fri, 23 Nov 2012 10:02:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bruno&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you please look into this one?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
